-- Connecticut Water Reports 37% Profit Gain After Acquisitions
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-05-09T18:15:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-09/connecticut-water-reports-37-profit-gain-after-acquisitions.html
Connecticut Water Service Inc. (CTWS) , the
largest publicly traded water provider in the U.S. Northeast,
reported first-quarter profit increased 37 percent to $2.6
million from a year earlier.  The Clinton, Connecticut-based company that supplies
drinking water to about 400,000 people acquired Maine Water Co.
and Biddeford & Saco Water Co. in 2012.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
